node.text: I was honored to have my good friend & celebrity makeup artist @danielmartin join me for the last episode of the season on @slumberpartywithtess!💖 THERE WERE TEARS LOL We talk about our similar paths to finding our creative outlets - starting at MAC, loving the Pacific Northwest, and finally creating our homes in cities surrounded by our chosen families.💄 Daniel shares some deep personal experiences like his 9/11 story and doing a client’s makeup for the last time for their memorial. We discuss how Daniel sets professional and personal boundaries - including turning down a potential client who happened to be a member of the Trump family.🤮 I am so grateful to have a friend like Daniel, and I think you’ll understand why by listening to this week’s episode! Listen now at the link in my bio, y’all! ✨

node.title: @danielmartin shares the Power & Purpose of his Work

node.text:
Lavern Rushin is so much more than Matthew Rushin’s mom—she’s a leader in her community and also runs @justice4matthewrushin. Lavern never thought that being a mother would mean becoming an advocate for her wrongfully incarcerated son, but that’s what happened. This week, we talk about getting justice for Matthew, which is an ongoing process, and what true justice for all could look like with significant reforms to our policing and legal systems.

We talk about the problems in policing as it stands today, and what defunding the police really means to people like Matthew, Lavern, and now to me, as well. Lavern’s tireless advocacy and legislative work will mean that fewer mothers are in her place in the future, and that - together - we are able to make reforms that keep our Black men and neuro-divergent family safe from police brutality and mass incarceration.

This week’s episode of @slumberpartywithtess hits home, and I hope you listen so that you can learn about Lavern’s work and what you can do to help—not to mention where Matthew is today and what his bright future has in store for him! To listen now, click the link in my bio✨ Also, make sure you follow @justice4matthewrushin to learn more about how you can help the Rushin family and to create the change we all need. #BlackLivesMatter

node.title: Justice for Matthew Rushin with his Mom, Lavern on #SlumberPartyPod

node.text: This week on #SlumberPartyPod, I met my insta-baddie friend @beerbottles_chainsaws IRL for the first time! We talked about how fashion brought us together and how it can bring all of us together, like when I see hot plus sized bbs on the street and compliment their outfits!🤣💖 Crystal is also the co-founder of an event production & creative company called @averygoodjob, along with her equally badass partner @kiesh.work. They have been crushing it during the pandemic by elevating Black voices and working with Black creatives to develop gorgeous, uniquely creative campaigns on social media and beyond. Tune in as Crystal shares her story (including a crazy ride over to the recording studio) and how she plans on working towards her goals today, and in the days, weeks, and months to come. Listen now and subscribe at the link in my bio!✨

node.title: Hanging out with Crystal Anderson IRL

node.text: This week, editor in Chief of Elle UK, @farrahstorr, the person who put me on the cover of Cosmo (!!) joins me from London!💖 Farrah and I talk about how we met, her experience as a journalist in the fashion world, where she finds compelling and transformative stories, and how she tells those stories beautifully using the UK’s top fashion magazines. We spoke about how Farrah’s editorial work grew out of her background as a writer, and why she believes that using fashion to tell stories is a powerful tool for creating social change. Farrah doesn’t aim to be controversial, but she definitely doesn’t shy away from the difficult conversations happening on social media and beyond—literally why I’m obsessed with her! Listen now and subscribe at the link in my bio!✨

node.title: Finding Strength by Embracing Discomfort with EIC of ELLE UK, Farrah Storr

node.text: I had such an incredible time meeting and getting to know my grandpas fav TV queen @kirstenvangsness, AKA Penelope Garcia, on this week’s episode of @slumberpartywithtess. node.text: This week, I got to talk to @LauraPrepon about everything from how we both got started as models to her experience as an actor and director, and even how she negotiates healthy boundaries with her online audience. It was so crazy talking to one of my teenage crushes—I mean who DIDN’T have a crush on Hot Donna?! Laura inspired me to take moments for myself and invest in planning ahead to be more centered in my everyday life - I hope she does the same for you! And don’t forget to check out her new line of kitchen tools, @PrepOnKitchen, available now on @HSN!✨ #SlumberPartyPod

node.title: @LauraPrepon on Being Prepared & Making Time for What Matters Most

node.text: This week on #SlumberPartyPod I got to hang out with fashion & entertainment icon @imisaacmizrahi! Pinch me!! 😱 It was so surreal to sit down with Isaac & talk about being fat & queer in fashion, why the arts are changing our youths’ lives & how we can support them more through the arts. I wore Isaac’s @target line blazer as a kid in rural Mississippi, so having the chance to interview him really felt like a career milestone! Listen to the full episode now & subscribe for more to come at the link in my bio, angels!💖

node.text: This week on @slumberpartywithtess, my dear friends and classroom heroes, Erin Gruwell of @freedomwritersfoundation and Debbie Fernandez @restorativelydeb, talk about restorative justice through education, how individual attention can transform lives, and doing the right thing when you're in a position to be helpful. Debbie specifically works with some of the most at risk - or as Erin says, at HOPE - students. Deb finds the hope in these kids and nurtures it. She makes these kids feel wanted, chosen & valued. Learn more about the work they both do and how incredibly important it is - not to mention how YOU can help - in this week’s episode of #SlumberPartyPod! Listen now at the link in my bio!

node.title: Working with At Hope Students with Debbie & Erin

node.text:
There’s so much going on all over the world- pain, loss, inhumanity, love, grief, rebirth… it’s endless it seems. I know I share a lot on here, we all do, but there’s so much that we don’t all discuss & that’s okay. I just want to send a big fat hug to all of y’all & let you know you’re loved regardless of what’s left unspoken. 💛

Hi from my first family vacay with my dad, step-mom, brother, and my two boys in Palm Springs y’all!🌴🌵 

I woke up here today and noticed the date - August 11th- 2 years ago today, I left my abusive relationship. Now, here I am with both of my boys, having reconnected with family & enjoying our time together, when I never imagined being here before.

It ain’t perfect, but I wanted to share this moment with y’all because 2 years ago, I didn’t want to even be alive. I was hurt, lost, and couldn’t picture a life that didn’t cause me pain. Today, life can still be challenging, duh, but I have developed the tools and support systems that I need to face those challenges. I have reconnected with family and disconnected from toxic elements that were in my life.

Healing is possible, y’all. I’m living proof. I couldn’t be here without my family (chosen and birth family), my community, or y’all - so thank you.💞ITS A HOT & HEALING GIRL SUMMER!!!! 

ALSO YES BOWIE LOST HIS FIRST TOOTH TODAY OMFG!!!??
